The paper deals with combinatorial group testing problems, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of extremal set theory also suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the investigation of adaptive versions of the models may fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
